The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The function parameter is declared as char *const *const argv, so the pointers point to char (non-const). The function does not modify the pointed-to strings and passes argv[i] to sscanf (which expects const char *). The pointer-to-non-const should instead be a pointer-to-const (e.g. const char *const *const argv). Thus Rule 8.13 is violated.
</scenario>

